# Homemade Pizza Lunch

## Servings: 4

## Time to prepare: 60-90 minutes

## Ingredients:

Dough
1 Tbs. active dry yeast
1 tsp. sugar
1 cup warm water (105° to 115°F)
3 cups all-purpose flour
1 tsp. salt
2 Tbs. extra-virgin olive oil

Sauce (marinara, pizza sauce, BBQ sauce, pesto, other?)

Cheeses (mozzarella, cheddar, parmesan cheese, provolone, goat cheese, other?)

Toppings (pepperoni, salami, peppers, sausage, mushrooms, anchovies, onions, pineapples, others?)

## Equipment needed:
- Oven
- 14" oven pizza baking tray
- Food processor
- Cutting board
- Knife
- Napkings

## Steps for preparation:
- Make dough by mixing dough ingredients in food processor (5 min)
- Cover dough with tea towel or foil and let dough rise for 1h at room temperature (60min)
- Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (15 min)
- Flatten dough into pizza tray (5 min)
- Spread sauce (5 min)
- Apply cheese (5 min)
- Apply toppings (5 min) 
- Place in oven for 45 min, let rest for 10 min before serving

